4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 3915 8550 3420 The output summer  is cleares at the star of each communation cycle.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 3585 8550 3660 during the commutation cycle, it accumulates the calue of each\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 150 1050 8550 3900 selected FIR filter.\001
-6
6 765 3150 3690 3465
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 2925 765 3285 The commutator index decrements by 1 modulo M.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 2835 765 3420 It is initially set to M-1,as shown on the diagram.\001
-6
6 495 4680 6480 7740
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 660 495 4815 Algorithm:\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 165 1410 495 5055 1. A sampe, x(n), arrives.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 5955 495 5295 2. A pointer to an FIR filter is selected from the Filter Pointer Ring as indexed by theCommutator Index.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 3705 495 5535 3. The sample, x(n) is sent to the FIR filter via the pointer access.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 5100 495 5775 4.  The FIR filter performs the convolution operation and sends its output to the summer.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 4170 495 6015 5. The summer adds the output value of the FIR filter to its current value.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 195 2745 495 6255 6.The commutator index is decremented by one.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 195 5820 495 6495 7, Steps 1 through 6 are repeated as each new sample, x(n) arrives until commutor index is equal to -1.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 2040 495 6735 8. IF comutator index is equal to -1.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 165 3105 495 6975 8.1 Comutator index is set back to M-1 (wrap around).\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 3750 495 7215 8.2 Summer contents are written to storage supplied by the caller.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 3255 495 7455 8.2 The summer is cleared for the next commutator cycle.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 2910 495 7695 9. The cycle repeats for the next M samples of x(n).\001
-6
6 7470 7155 10755 8055
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 2655 7470 7290 Input samples, x(n), are repeatedly swnt yo thr\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 150 2460 7470 7530 Decimator until a status of true is returned.\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 3285 7470 7770 At that point, the caller stores the returned output sample\001
4 0 0 50 0 0 12 0.0000 4 180 2895 7470 8010 into its memory buffer (one full decimation cycle).\001
